    <text type="letter"> 
        <body> 
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1888-03-20">2 P M March 20 '88</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute/>
            </opener>

            <p>It is a cloudy dark wet day&#8212;raining hard outside as I sit here by the
                window&#8212;am feeling pretty well&#8212;have just had my dinner, raw oysters &#38;
                a slice of boiled ham&#8212;enjoyed the meal&#8212;Get lots of invitations,
                applications &#38;c. every week&#8212;(O what lots of letters for
                autographs)&#8212;frequent visitors&#8212;sometimes an angel unawares&#8212;invites
                to swell dinners (or societies &#38;c) invariably declined&#8212;Am idle &#38;
                monotonous enough in my weeks &#38; life here&#8212;but upon the whole am mighty
                thankful it is no worse&#8212;my buying this shanty &#38; settling down here on
                &#189; or &#188; pay, &#38; getting Mrs. D[avis]<ptr target="n6113"/> to cook for me, <hi
                    rend="italic">might</hi> have been bettered by my disposing <hi
                    rend="italic">some other way</hi>&#8212;but I am satisfied it is all as well as it
                is&#8212;&#38; whatever happens.<ptr target="loc.07637_n2"/></p>

            <p>&#8212;Morse<ptr target="duk.00863_n3"/> is still out in Indiana with a probability of remaining&#8212;at least
                of not coming back here&#8212;I have not heard any thing definite of O'C[onnor]<ptr target="n2002"/>&#8212;I still jog away the
                <hi rend="italic">Herald</hi> bits<ptr target="n4133"/>&#8212;I enclose Mary Costelloe's<ptr target="loc.02189_n1"/> letter
                just rec'd&#8212;Isn't it cheery?</p>

            <closer>
                <salute/>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript><p>Send to Dr Bucke&#8212;both letters<ptr target="loc.07637_n1"/>&#8212;</p></postscript> 
        </body>
